# Generating secret in kubernetes (only for development)

> kubectl create secret generic jwt-secret --from-literal=JWT_KEY=asdfs2324fsdaf

# List ALL namespace

> kubectl get namespace

# List all services inside namespace

> kubectl get services -n <namespace>

# NATS Streaming Server

See 'Command Line Options' at [https://hub.docker.com/_/nats-streaming]

# NATS (any Service/Pods) - port forwarding command

> kubectl get pods

from above command result copy the pod name you wanted to make available from outside the kubernetes cluster, and run below command:

> kubectl port-forward <POD_NAME> 4222:4222

- first port (4222): port on local machine through which request goes from local machine
- second port (4222): port inside the pod that local machine trying to access
